15 SUMMARY
1166 This bill repeals the law governing the certified visual media production tax credit. It
1177 increases reimbursements under the laws governing the visual media production
1188 reimbursement and places limits on those reimbursements. It changes the definition of
1199 "visual media production expense" and requires an applicant for a visual media production
2200 certificate to agree to withhold a percentage of payments made to an entity created to hire
2211 out the services of one individual.
